<p>
Vieques is a short flight from San Juan, Puerto Rico, or a bit longer trip by ferry from Fajardo (a town on the east coast of the island of Puerto Rico).
</p>
<h4>Getting to Puerto Rico</h4>
<p>
Flights to San Juan, Puerto Rico can be booked from pretty much anywhere in the US. The airport code is SJU. 
</p>
<p>
(We will hopefully be arranging for a modest group discount through American Airlines, and we will post directions on how to take advantage as soon as we can!)
</p>
<h4>Getting to Vieques</h4>
<p>
You can get to Vieques from San Juan either <a href="#plane">by plane</a> or <a href="#ferry">by ferry</a>.
</p>
<a name="plane"></a>
<h5>By Plane</h5>
<p>
Theoretically, you can fly straight from SJU to Vieques, but, best we can tell, itâ€™s crazy expensive, so we would not recommend it. There is a small regional airport (Isla Grande - SIG) a short taxi ride from SJU, and from there you can choose from a few airlines that will fly to Vieques.  Note that these are fairly small planes, but the trip is very short.
</p>
