<a name="ferry"></a>
<h5>By Ferry</h5>
<p>
If you can get to Fajardo, taking the ferry is a cheap option. It requires more planning and is probably only worth it if you are traveling with one or more other people (You can also rent a car one way from San Juan to Fajardo through a number of car rental companies).
</p>
<p>
A tax from SJU to Fajardo is about $80.  The Ferry itself costs $2 each way for adults 60 and under and $1 each way for adults over 60
</p>
